    {
      "id": "ddabb95ba2851d9968d295106f57531d2366f91d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-12 05:16:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis will cause more memory allocation for all of the histograms, even though it is not needed in the vast majority of cases. \n\nI'm already working on a patch to do dynamic allocation of the histogram structure (in chunks of 16 buckets at one time) so that it does not need to be allocated at the maximum size, and in fact will save done memory in the common cases. \n\nIt will take me a little while to post it, since in traveling and the patch is still in the coding stage, but I think that is a better long-term solution.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bcfd9b82180a531b1f6e2d235433068af65d74a0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 373,
        "name": "Ryan Haasken",
        "email": "haasken@cray.com",
        "username": "rhaasken"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-14 14:56:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, thanks for your comments.  I agree that dynamic allocation is a better long-term solution.  I will abandon this patch.  Please copy me on the new patch when you submit it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4eb18d6eb96a24e8ae3ddf784853b0098ce0522a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 373,
        "name": "Ryan Haasken",
        "email": "haasken@cray.com",
        "username": "rhaasken"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-14 14:57:29.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nAbandoning in favor of the long-term solution that Andreas has in the works.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fab0b93c2a9e077eda78be8424a6d5767a3fcee6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-08-17 16:50:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas,\n\nAny chance of that patch soon?  (I would be willing to take it and work on it.)  We're starting to have real need of this.\n\nOtherwise, I feel like this patch is fine.  Isn't the extra memory usage just sizeof(unsigned long)*(256-32)*num_OSTs?\n\nSo, on a real system (let's make it a really big one):\n8 bytes*224*2048 = ~3.5 MiB.  That's pretty trivial, in the most extreme case we can come up with.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
  ],
